Hey! I am Praveen Venkatesh from Indian Institute of Technology Gandhinagar

  • Senior undergrad at IITGN

  • Passionate about image understanding in robotics applications, applied deep learning.

  • Currently diving into the complexities of multi-agent robotic systems!

  • Love tinkering around with electronics and experimenting with crazy ideas. Check my projects out here: Projects

  • Absolutely love teaching and disseminating knowledge in intuitive ways - my projects always have a visual component to it :)

I am a senior undergrad student in Electrical Engineering at IIT Gandhinagar, specializing in Robotics. In my spare time, I engage myself in tinkering with electronics and automating my life. I have always firmly believed that we should strive to be the best version of ourselves, and have transformed significantly as a person during my time at IITGN. Over the course of three and a half years at IITGN, I have been part of several student-run groups and developmental projects, and have actively contributed towards improving the sporting and technical culture at the institute.

Some things about me:

    • I go on typeracer and have fun when I feel like it. Its how I can type at 100 WPM :P

    • Music = ❤️

    • I can play the Keyboard, and can play a few tunes on the flute.

    • I can Yodel! (Although people find yodelling irritating 😜)

    • I play a lot of games! (gamerTag - flyingMango)
